  <h1>Executive Summary</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    bearerCORE&#8482; is a protocol-grade <strong>CBDC</strong> infrastructure that enables African
    central banks to issue, validate, and settle sovereign digital currency across all 54 corridors
    of the African Union &mdash;without requiring recipients to hold a bank account.
  </p>

  <p>
    Modelled on the physical cash metaphor &mdash;where possession equals ownership &mdash;bearerCORE&#8482;
    introduces the <strong>CVIB</strong> (Central Bank Issuance Bill): a cryptographically signed
    digital banknote that is minted by a central bank, delivered as <strong>Digital Money Bundles</strong>
    via secure SFTP/NAS channels to commercial banks, and redeemable instantly by any holder,
    anywhere on the continent.
  </p>

  <p>
    Unlike account-based CBDC systems that replicate commercial banking infrastructure,
    bearerCORE&#8482; operates as a <strong>bearer instrument</strong>. Each CVIB
    carries its own value, identity, and provenance inside the file itself &mdash;enabling offline
    storage, peer-to-peer transfer, and settlement without intermediary custody.
  </p>

  <div class="stat-row">
