    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <span class="stat-number">350M+</span>
      <span class="stat-label">Unbanked Africans Targeted</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat">
      <span class="stat-number">&lt;2s</span>
      <span class="stat-label">Cross-Border Settlement</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    The protocol is production-ready. A desktop minting station (Qt6, macOS ARM64) handles
    CVIB issuance at the central bank level. A Rails 7 API validation desk handles commercial
    bank ingestion, CBDC registry checks, and full lifecycle audit. Both layers are connected
    through a governance engine that enforces corridor rules, FX rates, and reserve backing.
  </p>

