  <h1>Governance &amp; Pilot Programme</h1>

  <h2>Governance Framework</h2>

  <p>
    bearerCORE&#8482; is designed for central bank sovereignty. No private entity controls
    the protocol. Each participating central bank retains full authority over its issuance
    parameters, corridor eligibility, and redemption policies. Cross-corridor governance
    decisions &mdash;such as adjusting FX rate oracles or modifying liquidity lock requirements &mdash;
    are made through a structured proposal and voting mechanism requiring supermajority
    approval from affected central banks.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Governance proposals:</strong> Submitted on-chain, timestamped, and immutable</li>
    <li><strong>Voting thresholds:</strong> Configurable per corridor; default 67% supermajority</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency freeze:</strong> Any central bank governor may freeze bundles in their jurisdiction unilaterally</li>
    <li><strong>Full audit trail:</strong> Every CVIB lifecycle event &mdash;minting, delivery, validation, transfer, redemption &mdash;is logged with cryptographic linkage</li>
    <li><strong>Real-Time Corridor Surveillance:</strong> Central Bank Governors maintain a Command Center view of all 1,431 bilateral corridors, allowing for instant adjustments to liquidity pools and risk limits to protect national currency stability</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="gauge-wrap">
